<sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;can/can't&lt;/I&gt; + verb to talk about ability.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_3_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_3_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can sing&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; but I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can't dance&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_3_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>My father &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can speak German&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; and Russian but he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can't speak French&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text2a><titlesound2>%undefined</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>%undefined</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>%undefined</sound3><text3a>%undefined</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>%undefined</sound4><text4a>%undefined</text4a></section>
<section><title>&lt;I&gt;Can/can't&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;can&lt;/I&gt; + subject + verb to make questions.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_3_2_4.mp3</titlesound><text1>Karen &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can play&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; football.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_3_2_5.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Can Karen play&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; football.</text1a><text2>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;can play&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; tennis.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_3_2_6.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Can you play&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; tennis?</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_3_2_7.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>&lt;I&gt;Can&lt;/I&gt; is a modal verb. Modal verbs do not change their form.</sectiontitle2><text3>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;We can&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; speak English.</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_3_2_8.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;He can&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; speak English.</text3a><text4>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;I can't &lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;use a computer.</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_3_2_9.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;She can't &lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;use a computer.</text4a></section></grammar>